                            </div>
                            <div class="homepage-card-content">
                                <div class="newstab-card-content">
                                    <div class="newstab-card-title" data-tooltip="From Control to Connectivity: This Month’s New Development Platforms" data-tooltip-position="top-center">
                                        From Control to Connectivity: This Month’s New Development Platforms
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="newstab-card-desc">This month’s Microchip development tool releases enable early subsystem validation—helping engineering teams reduce integration risk and accelerate time to market.</div>
                                    <div class="news-tab-anchor">
                                        <a href="https://www.microchip.com/en-us/about/media-center/blog/2026/from-control-to-connectivity-new-development-platforms" target="_blank" aria-label="Learn more about From Control to Connectivity: This Month’s New Development Platforms"> <i class="fas fa-long-arrow-right"></i> Learn more"</a>
                                    </div>

                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    
                        <div class="newstab-card">
                            <div class="homepage-card-img">
                                <img src="/content/dam/mchp/microsolutions/PyKit-Explorer-Hero.png" alt="Meet the PyKit Explorer: The CircuitPython Development Kit That Lives on Your Desk"/>
                            </div>
                            <div class="homepage-card-content">
                                <div class="newstab-card-content">
                                    <div class="newstab-card-title" data-tooltip="Meet the PyKit Explorer: The CircuitPython Development Kit That Lives on Your Desk" data-tooltip-position="top-center">
                                        Meet the PyKit Explorer: The CircuitPython Development Kit That Lives on Your Desk
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="newstab-card-desc">Designed for learning, built like real hardware. Meet the Microchip Curiosity PyKit Explorer—a CircuitPython development kit designed to stay on your desk, not in a drawer. Featuring a SAME51 MCU, TFT display, IMU, sensors, audio and BLE, it enables engineers and students to go from LED blink to full games, all while reinforcing real embedded design concepts.</div>
                                    <div class="news-tab-anchor">
                                        <a href="https://www.microchip.com/en-us/about/media-center/blog/2026/pykit-explorer-circuitpython-development-kit" target="_blank" aria-label="Learn more about Meet the PyKit Explorer: The CircuitPython Development Kit That Lives on Your Desk"> <i class="fas fa-long-arrow-right"></i> Learn more"</a>
                                    </div>

                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
